Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDid%20it%20resonate%20on%20a%20personal%20level%20for%20you%20with%20anything%20that%20you'd%20experienced%20in%20your%20own%20life%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYes%2C%20of%20course.%20I'm%20an%20American%20citizen%2C%20but%20I%20was%20born%20in%20Brazil.%20I%20grew%20up%20in%20Brazil.%20I've%20been%20living%20here%20for%20less%20than%2010%20years%20only.%20And%20I%20always%20thought%20about%2C%20how%20would%20I%20react%20if%20I%20was%20somewhere%20and%20someone%20would%20see%20me%20speaking%20with%20this%20accent%20and%20go%20like%2C%20%26quot%3BWhat%20are%20you%20doing%20here%3F%20What's%20your%20business%20here%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20don't%20know%20what%20I%20would%20do.%20Would%20I%20react%20violently%3F%20Would%20I%20say%20something%20back%3F%20Would%20I%20just%20go%3F%20I%20don't%20know.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20uncertainty%20really%20hit%20me%20in%20that%20scene%20with%20Jesse.%20My%20character%20Joel%20is%20the%20character%20in%20the%20film%20that%20has%20the%20word%20as%20a%20weapon%20%E2%80%94%20he's%20the%20writer%2C%20he%20can%20speak.%20But%20slowly%2C%20slowly%2C%20slowly%2C%20all%20his%20repertoire%20of%20words%20just%20disappears%20because%20of%20facing%20that%20amount%20of%20violence%20and%20prejudice.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EOne%20of%20the%20most%20intense%20scenes%20for%20me%20was%20right%20after%20that%2C%20in%20the%20car%20when%20Joel%20and%20Cailee%20Spaeny's%20character%20Jessie%20are%20both%20screaming%20and%20hyperventilating.%20How%20did%20you%20get%20into%20that%20mindset%2C%20and%20how%20did%20you%20get%20out%20of%20it%20after%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20whole%20mass%20grave%20scene%20took%20us%20two%20days%20to%20shoot.%20It%20was%20very%20intense%2C%20very%20hardcore%20like%20I%20said.%20The%20last%20day%2C%20I%20laid%20down.%20I%20was%20exhausted%20and%20I%20cried%2C%20and%20I%20just%20let%20it%20go.%20And%20then%20we%20started%20shooting%20other%20scenes%20be