%20League%26quot%3B%20movie%20%E2%80%94%20but%20was%20there%20a%20fat%20enough%20check%20from%20anything%20in%20that%20decade%20that%20provided%20you%20some%20kind%20of%20stability%20until%20the%20big%20break%20came%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20know%2C%20I'm%20a%20poor%20kid%20from%20Georgia.%20I%20come%20from%20very%20humble%20beginnings%20and%20I've%20never%20been%20afraid%20of%20work%20in%20my%20life.%20I%20moved%20to%20Los%20Angeles%20when%20I%20was%2019%20years%20old.%20I%20had%20%24300%20in%20my%20pocket.%20I%20had%20enough%20to%20last%20a%20month.%20And%20the%20first%20morning%20I%20was%20in%20LA%20I%20had%20a%20job%20at%20a%20health%20club.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20did%20that%20until%20I%20decided%20I%20was%20going%20to%20start%20my%20own%20business%2C%20and%20I%20started%20a%20valet%20parking%20company.%20I%20had%20that%20for%20a%20couple%20of%20years.%20I%20sold%20cowboy%20boots.%20I%20became%20a%20personal%20trainer.%20But%20along%20with%20all%20of%20that%20I%20was%20very%20fortunate%20to%20start%20working%20as%20an%20actor%20straight%20away.%20But%20I'm%20conservative%2C%20fiscally%20speaking%2C%20so%20I%20continued%20to%20keep%20working%20side%20jobs%20and%20structured%20my%20life%20in%20a%20way%20that%20I%20had%20a%20job%20that%20allowed%20me%20to%20walk%20away%20whenever%20an%20opportunity%20to%20act%20came%20up.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20I%20actually%20continued%20to%20have%20side%20jobs%20for%20five%20years%20past%20the%20point%20of%20needing%20those%20jobs.%20I%20took%20all%20the%20money%20I%20was%20making%20from%20storytelling%20and%20just%20put%20that%20in%20the%20bank.%20I%20lived%20off%20what%20I%20was%20making%20on%20these%20side%20gigs.%20That's%20how%20I%20structured%20my%20money.%20And%20when%20I%20finally%20made%20the%20decision%20to%20go%20with%20acting%20as%20the%20sole%20income%2C%20by%20then%20I%20had%20my%20manager.%20It%20was%20when%20I%20got%20the%20role%20in%20%26quot%3BThe%20Apostle.%26quot%3B%20That's%20when%20I%20decided%20I%20felt%20confident%20enough%20that%20I%20had%20enough%20cushion%20to%20really%20go%20for%20it.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Apostle%26quot%3B%20came%20out%20in%201997.%20It%20was%20a%20critical%20darling%2C%20Duvall%20got%20an%20Oscar%20nomination%2C%20so%20the%20movie%20got%20a%20lot%20of%20attention.%20Then%2C%20a%20few%20years%20later%2C%20the%20FX%20series%20%26quot%3BThe%20Shield%26quot%3B%20changed%20everything%20for%20you.%20Was%20there%20a%20moment%20during%20the%20run%20of%20that%20show%20where%20you%20thought%20to%20yourself%2C%20I%20can%20now%20call%20myself%20a%20star%2C%20not%20just%20a%20working%20actor%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWell%2C%20the%20very%20first%20episode%20they%20wanted%20to%20fire%20me%20%E2%80%94%20the%20higher-ups.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShawn%20Ryan%2C%20the%20creator%20of%20the%20show%2C%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20just%20saw%20this%20kid%20in%20'The%20Apostle%2C'%20let%20me%20write%20an%20episode%20for%20him.%26quot%3B%20And%20so%20episode%20number%20two%20was%20really%20kind%20of%20about%20my%20character.%20And%20%5Bthen%5D%20the%20brass%20saw%20it%20and%20were%20like%2C%20%26quot%3BHe's%20our%20guy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBecoming%20a%20star%20was%20never%20my%20intention.%20That%20was%20never%20the%20reason%20why%20I%20got%20into%20this%20in%20the%20first%20place.%20It's%20weird%2C%20I%20look%20back%20on%20my%20life%20as%20a%20storyteller%2C%20and%20though%20there%20were%20dips%2C%20it%20was%20always%20going%20up.%20And%20I%20think%20that's%20because%20there%20was%20never%20an%20opportunity%20I%20wasn't%20ready%20to%20step%20into.%20And%20I%20think%20God%2C%20whoever%20she%20is%2C%20structured%20my%20life%20in%20that%20way.%20I%20have%20been%20ready%20for%20every%20moment%20that%20has%20come%20my%20way.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20it%20had%20been%20different%20in%20any%20way%2C%20I%20think%20I%20would%20have%20left%20the%20business.%20I%20don't%20think%20it%20would%20have%20worked%20out%20for%20me.%20So%2