0the%20US%20share%20of%20the%20global%20chip-making%20market.%20Between%201990%20and%202020%2C%20the%20number%20of%20chips%20made%20in%20the%20United%20States%20fell%20by%20a%20third.%20In%20that%20same%20period%2C%20Taiwan%2C%20China%2C%20and%20South%20Korea's%20combined%20share%20grew%20by%20almost%2060%25%2C%20the%20Journal%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20United%20States%20is%20eager%20to%20control%20chip%20manufacturing%20as%20artificial%20intelligence%20becomes%20critical%20in%20national%20and%20international%20security.%20Since%20%26quot%3Bgeneral-purpose%20AI%20software%2C%20datasets%2C%20and%20algorithms%20are%20not%20effective%20targets%20for%20controls%2C%20the%20attention%20naturally%20falls%20on%20the%20computer%20hardware%20necessary%20to%20implement%20modern%20AI%20systems%2C%26quot%3B%20Saif%20M.%20Khan%20and%20Alexander%20Mann%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcset.georgetown.edu%2Fpublication%2Fai-chips-what-they-are-and-why-they-matter%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewrote%20in%20a%20Center%20for%20Security%20and%20Emerging%20Technology%20report%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20edge%20in%20chip%20manufacturing%20would%20help%20the%20United%20States%20maintain%20global%20dominance.%20%26quot%3BGiven%20the%20foundational%20nature%20of%20certain%20technologies%2C%20such%20as%20advanced%20logic%20and%20memory%20chips%2C%20we%20must%20maintain%20as%20large%20of%20a%20lead%20as%20possible%2C%26quot%3B%20national%20security%20advisor%20Jake%20Sullivan%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.whitehouse.gov%2Fbriefing-room%2Fspeeches-remarks%2F2022%2F09%2F16%2Fremarks-by-national-security-advisor-jake-sullivan-at-the-special-competitive-studies-project-global-emerging-technologies-summit%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%20in%20a%20speech%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChip%20manufacturing%2C%20however%2C%20is%20the%20industry's%20largest%20cost%20driver%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mckinsey.com%2Findustries%2Fs