ny%20unwanted%20charges%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20I%20called%20my%20insurance%20ahead%20of%20time%20to%20make%20sure%20that%20the%20prescribed%20scan%20would%20be%20covered.%20They%20confirmed%20that%20the%20scan%20listed%20on%20the%20referral%20would%20be%20fully%20covered%2C%20and%20that%20the%20coverage%20would%20kick%20in%20before%20I%20met%20my%20deductible%20(which%20was%20great%20since%20it%20had%20just%20reset%20for%20the%20year).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESure%20enough%2C%20my%20insurance%20portal%20showed%20that%20I%20owed%20%240%20for%20the%20prescribed%20scan%2C%20but%20I%20was%20also%20being%20charged%20for%20a%20mysterious%20second%20service%20I%20didn't%20recognize.%20I%20called%20the%20provider%2C%20thinking%20I%20must%20have%20been%20charged%20by%20accident%2C%20but%20they%20informed%20me%20that%20the%20other%20test%20was%20a%20complementary%20study%20they%20always%20performed%20alongside%20the%20one%20I'd%20gone%20in%20for.%20The%20test%20took%20place%20simultaneously%20in%20the%20same%20machine%2C%20so%20I%20had%20no%20idea%20I%20was%20receiving%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20look%20back%20at%20my%20doctor's%20referral%20confirmed%20that%20she'd%20only%20ordered%20one%20scan%2C%20so%20I%20decided%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftiktok-simple-trick-lower-hospital-bill-viral-2020-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edispute%20the%20bill%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%20I'd%20scheduled%20one%20service%2C%20submitted%20the%20proper%20referral%20for%20it%2C%20and%20confirmed%20coverage%20with%20my%20insurance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20I%20had%20that%20referral%20as%20proof%20of%20my%20doctor's%20order%2C%20the%20provider%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fitemized-bill%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eacknowledged%20the%20discrepancy%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20the%20charge%20was%20reduced%20to%20zero.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ETip%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Trying%20to%20compare%20referrals%2C%20bills%2C%20and%20insuranc