ecause%20of%20high%20prices%20in%20the%20US.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EJensen%20said%20her%20apartment%20in%20Ecuador%20would%20cost%20three%20times%20as%20much%20in%20her%20home%20state%20of%20Montana.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EMontana%20is%20among%20the%20western%20states%20where%20high%20housing%20costs%20are%20pricing%20out%20some%20locals.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20is%20an%20as-told-to%20essay%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%2071-year-old%20Lonita%20Jensen%2C%20a%20retired%20nurse%20who%20is%20from%20Montana%20but%20currently%20living%20in%20Ecuador.%20Business%20Insider%20has%20verified%20the%20rental%20prices.%20The%20essay%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20grew%20up%20in%20Billings%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmontana-mountain-town-seeley-lake-largest-employer-closes-costs-housing-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMontana%3C%2Fa%3E.%20I%20was%20born%20and%20raised%20there.%20I%20never%20left%20Montana%20until%20I%20was%20in%20my%20thirties.%20I%20went%20to%20college%20in%20Bozeman.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20husband%20was%20in%20construction%2C%20and%20we%20ended%20up%20moving%20a%20lot%20when%20I%20was%20in%20my%20thirties.%20So%20I've%20lived%20in%20other%20places%2C%20but%20I%20keep%20coming%20back%20to%20Montana.%20But%20then%20the%20last%20time%20I%20tried%20to%20come%20back%2C%20the%20prices%20had%20just%20gone%20up%20so%20high.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20a%20nurse%2C%20but%20I%20retired%20to%20become%20the%20nanny%20for%20my%20grandson%20in%20Dallas.%20I%20did%20that%20for%20three%20years%2C%20and%20then%20I%20couldn't%20survive%20down%20there.%20It%20was%20so%20expensive.%20So%20I%20checked%20Montana%20because%20my%20daughter%20lives%20there%2C%20and%20that%20wasn't%20going%20to%20work%20either%20because%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Faffordable-housing-crisis-us-west-coast-cause-explained-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erents%20were%20so%20high%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20sister%20had%20come%20down%20to%20Ecuador%20and%20she%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BWell%2C%20you%20can%20afford%20to%20live%20down%20here.%26quot%3B%20So%20that's%20why%20I%20ended%20up%20here%20about%20four%20years%20ago.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20in%20a%20city%20called%20Cuenca%20at%20the%20base%20of%20the%20Andes.%20My%20kids%20all%20want%20me%20to%20come%20home%20to%20the%20US.%20I%20have%20six%20grandchildren%20and%20one%20great-granddaughter%2C%20and%20I%20would%20love%20to%20go%20back%2C%20but%20they%20all%20live%20in%20a%20place%20that%20I%20can't%20afford%20%E2%80%94%20Billings%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcolorado-ski-town-steamboat-springs-high-housing-costs-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESteamboat%20Springs%2C%20Colorado%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20Dallas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20really%20sad.%20I'd%20like%20to%20be%20by%20my%20grandkids%20and%20my%20kids%2C%20and%20it's%20just%20not%20possible.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EEcuador%20is%20beautiful%20and%20a%20lot%20cheaper%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20would%20move%20back%20to%20Billings%20if%20I%20could.%20It's%20only%2060%20miles%20from%20Red%20Lodge%2C%20which%20is%20one%20of%20the%20entrances%20up%20over%20the%20Beartooth%20Highway%20into%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fyellowstone-150-years-beautiful-photos-2022-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EYellowstone%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Cuenca%2C%20I%20pay%20%24750%20for%20three%20bedrooms%2C%20three%20and%20a%20half%20baths%2C%20and%20a%20private%20patio.%20Something%20Similar%20to%20this%20in%20Billings%20would%20be%20about%20%242%2C400%20a%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20climate%20is%20beautiful%20in%20Cuenca.%20It%20stays%20pretty%20much%20the%20same%20year%20round%20and%20we%20don't%20get%20snow%2C%20but%20I%20grew%20up%20in%20snow%2C%20so%20it's%20not%20like%20I%20can't%20handle%20it.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPeople%20are%20very%20nice%20here.%20Fresh%20fruits%20and%20fresh%20vegetables%20are%20very%20cheap%20here.%20There's%20affordable%20healthcare%20here.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222234%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22View%20of%20the%20city%20of%20Cuenca%2C%20Ecuador%2C%20with%20it's%20many%20churches%20and%20rooftops%2C%20on%20a%20cloudy%20day%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F661861841caec1275a6f614f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221342%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ECuenca%2C%20Ecuador%2C%20is%20located%20at%20the%20base%20of%20the%20Andes%20and%20has%20attracted%20a%20lot%20of%20US%20expats.%3Cp%3EAlanFalcony%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20sister%20was%20living%20here%20when%20I%20moved%2C%20so%20I%20met%20people%20through%20her.%20But%20if%20she%20wouldn't%20have%20been%20here%2C%20it%20would've%20been%20a%20whole%20lot%20scarier.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20quite%20an%20expat%20community%20here%20and%20a%20lot%20of%20single%20women.%20Maybe%20they've%20had%20a%20loss%20of%20a%20spouse%2C%20which%20I%20have%20had%2C%20or%20they%20just%20didn't%20make%20as%20much%20money%20in%20the%20workforce%2C%20so%20they%20didn't%20have%20the%20resources%20to%20stay%20in%20the%20states%20because%20things%20have%20gotten%20so%20expensive.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20men%20here%20too.%20Most%20of%20them%20have%20pretty%20much%20the%20same%20story.%20They%20can't%20afford%20to%20live%20in%20the%20states%20anymore.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EPretty%20places%20are%20getting%20too%20expensive%20to%20live%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20tell%20my%20kids%20I%20couldn't%20come%20back%20to%20Montana%20or%20to%20Colorado%20or%20any%20of%20those%20places%20without%20going%20back%20to%20work%20full%20time.%20All%20I%20have%20is%20social%20security%2C%20and%20I'm%20almost%2072.%20I%20can't%20bend%20over%20like%20I%20did%20for%20surgeries%20for%20hours%20on%20end%20like%20I%20used%20to.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20thing%20I%20miss%