hild%20Rights%20(CPCR)%20Act%2C%202005%20after%20its%20inquiry%20under%20Section%2014%20of%20CRPC%20Act%202005%20concluded%20that%20there%20is%20no%20'health%20drink'%20defined%20under%20FSS%20Act%202006%2C%20rules%20and%20regulations%20submitted%20by%20FSSAI%20and%20Mondelez%20India%20Food%20Pvt%20Ltd%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20ministry%20said%20in%20a%20notification%2C%20dated%20April%2010.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20advisory%20comes%20on%20the%20back%20of%20an%20investigation%20by%20the%20NCPCR%20that%20found%20the%20Bournvita%20contains%20sugar%20levels%2C%20much%20above%20the%20acceptable%20limits.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEarlier%2C%20the%20NCPCR%20had%20called%20upon%20the%20Food%20Safety%20and%20Standards%20Authority%20of%20India%20(FSSAI)%20to%20initiate%20action%20against%20the%20companies%20that%20failed%20to%20meet%20safety%20standards%20and%20guidelines%20and%20were%20projecting%20power%20supplements%20as%20'health%20drinks'.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENotably%2C%20as%20per%20the%20regulatory%20body%2C%20'health%20drink'%20has%20not%20been%20defined%20in%20the%20country's%20food%20laws%20and%20to%20project%20something%20under%20the%20same%20violates%20the%20rules.%20The%20FSSAI%2C%20earlier%20this%20month%2C%20also%20instructed%20e-commerce%20portals%20against%20labelling%20diary-based%20or%20malt-based%20beverages%20as%20'health%20drinks'.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20controversy%20over%20the%20'unhealthy'%20nature%20of%20Bournvita%20first%20arose%20after%20a%20YouTuber%20in%20his%20video%20slammed%20the%20powder%20supplement%20and%20informed%20that%20it%20contained%20excessive%20sugar%2C%20cocoa%20solids%20and%20harmful%20colourants%20that%20could%20lead%20to%20serious%20health%20hazards%20in%20children%2C%20including%20cancer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1712998560000%2C%22visual%22%3